osts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 6:22:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=882.topic>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.shadowsting.com/TK/xen.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pet Taunt and Nuke Aggro</span><hr size=1> Hello fellow mages, I have been playing around with my new 61 air pet in groups and I am trying to find the best way to minimize my aggro.<br>
<br>
It seems that the epic pet had a much better taunt than the 61 air pet.  Meaning that if I was in a group with a non-pet tanking, I could nuke a lot more without pulling aggro if my epic had his taunt on.  (Several of our guild wizards concurred with me on this point, and say this hold true for raid mobs as well, specifically with the epic pet)  This doesn't seem to work as well with my air pet.<br>
<br>
Based on Raz's reccomendations, I do want to get Spell Casting Subtlety at some point, but I'm a ways off from that at the moment.<br>
<br>
What are your experiences with /pet taunt and nuking?  Should I leave taunt off in xp groups, or does it allow me to nuke more without pulling aggro?<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=320028" target="_blank">Xenditil</a><BR>
63 Arch Mage<BR>
The Kindred<BR>
