<br>
If you're in a group, the MA is the one who keeps the aggro.  You're pet taunting won't make much difference.  I leave mine on most of the time anyway, pet will never out-taunt a PC of any type (game is coded that way) so it's not like the mob is going to leave the MA and start chasing the pet.<br>
<br>
As far as soloing however, I do agree that Epic has more taunt power.  I believe the combination of its stun spells and proc damage really keep those mobs ticked off. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I basically have to cast FoT early in the fight and then sit down to pull aggro off my pet.  Which I try not to do of course.  So I don't plan on buying subtlety AA really.  I have a lot of other things on my list before that would happen.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xenditil>Xenditil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(12/19/02 7:30:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=882.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.shadowsting.com/TK/xen.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Taunt and Nuke Aggro</span><hr size=1> I understand that the pet will not get aggro over a PC, but I've had guild wizards tell me that having a pet in a fight seems to help them nuke more.  I guess that's what my question was about, to see if anyone else has seen thins.<br>
<br>
I don't pull aggro in raid situations that often, but I am interested in finding out how to reduce aggro for single groups.  The other night I was grouped with a 65 warrior with an enraging blow weapon, and I still had to be very careful about my nuking not to pull aggro.<br>
I was using FoT exclusively, and my air pet with taunt on.<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=320028" target="_blank">Xenditil</a><BR>
